Key Match Events: David Fry hit a go-ahead, two-run homer in the seventh inning
Emmanuel Clase preserved a 4-3 lead in the eighth inning by striking out Trey Sweeney
Brayan Rocchio scored on a bunt by David Fry in the ninth inning
Post-Match Reflections: Stephen Vogt commented on David Fry's performance
A.J. Hinch expressed confidence in Tarik Skubal for Game 5
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cleveland ended a streak of 11 losses in postseason elimination games
The game was played at Comerica Park with a record-breaking attendance of 44,923 fans
Others: The winner of Game 5 will advance to the AL Championship Series against the Yankees in New York starting Monday
